The first '''robotic-assisted double heart valve replacement''' was carried out in the Chennai region of India at Chettinad Hospital. Considered a rare form of surgery, this is the first instance of such a procedure using [[robotic surgery]].<ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Rare-robotic-surgery-done-in-city-hospital/articleshow/7631028.cms</ref> The surgery was carried out by Dr R Ravi Kumar, who is the director of the Institute of Cardiovascular Disease and head of robotic surgery centre at the Chettinad Health clinic.<ref>http://www.thehindu.com/health/medicine-and-research/article1510263.ece</ref>

